The paper deals with exact uniform sampling of Catalan structures, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DM, cs.CC). The use of a unique matrix and a linear height tree suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures and algorithms sub-category (cs.DS). The mention of triangulations of convex polygons and monotonic lattice paths suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the mention of optimal coding and optimal number of random bits required for the algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
